==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|Cristiente}}, {{m|enm|Cristente}}, borrowed from {{der|en|fro|crestienté}}, from {{der|en|ML.|-}} stem of {{m|la|Chrīstiānitās|}}, from {{der|en|la|christianus}}, {{m|la|Christianus}}, from {{der|en|grc|Χριστιανός}}, from {{m|grc|Χριστός||Christ, anointed one}} + Latin {{m|la|-anus||suffix for of, related to}} + one more suffix borrowed from Latin "ity" makes the final {{suffix|en|Christian|ity}}. The term was respelled in the early modern English period to more closely reflect its Latin etymon.

